<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-15T12:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-15T12:29:00-05:00" n="448" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1091</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-15T12:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1917,
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Military conditions unchanged. Government troops to-day were in touch
                            with forces under Gómez near line between Santa Clara and Camaguey
                            Provinces but are awaiting arrival of regiment sent by sea from Habana
                            before attacking.</p>
                        <pb facs="0525" n="359" xml:id="pg_359"/>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petrel</hi> of naval station is at Santiago. Consul
                            there again reports conditions growing worse but no details.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>